				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: SWTOR To Introduce a Gay Planet
				</h2>
				

						
						
							
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1769336">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Nah, it's a huge thing. You cannot just make the dialogue accessable to same sex characters - that doesn't work at all. that's one of the things Bioware did well with the SGR in Mass Effect 3 - they were actually SGR and not just complete carbon copies of the straight relationships. <br />
<br />
I'd really like to get up in arms about this and all, but honestly I understand why they have to do it this way and it makes sense. It's bad press but slamming one of the best LGBT companies out there (not just in gaming but in general) for this is really self-defeating I think. No insult or offense is intended, they aren't trying to segregate gay people onto just one planet, it's just the limitations of their game and the fact they were rushed to launch and so couldn't implement. Everything else new to the game will be locked to the new world, so will the SGR. When the next expansion pack comes out and the level cap goes up again we'll see more SGR elsewhere in the game. <br />
<br />
No-one can ever accuse Bioware of not being supportive of SGR.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
